1602129600.title: Bargain Hunt
1602129600.descr: Two teams of amateur antique collectors meet at an antiques fair to compete to make the largest profit from a three hundred pound budget. Once the contestants have done the shopping for their own items, the experts then take any leftover money and go shopping for more antiques which is 'bonus buys'. The teams then have to decide whether or not to take these items to auction.

1602132300.title: Last of the Summer Wine
1602132300.descr: Clegg is writing his memoirs, but is having trouble remembering people's names; Clegg, Truly and Billy meet a man who wants to sail to Ilkley in an inflatable swan, unfortunately it has developed a puncture which Entwistle repairs; Clegg climbs a tree so he can see the church clock, unfortunately he gets stuck; Tom and Entwistle try to cheer Smiler up after he has been dumped by Hermione.

1602134100.title: Call the Midwife
1602134100.descr: Period drama series set in East London in the 1950s, following the life and work of a young midwife Jenny Lee and her colleagues at the Nonnatus House nursing convent. They serve the poor society of Poplar, London. Their main duty is to help bring safe birth to women and help them look after their newborns.

1602137400.title: DIY SOS: The Big Build
1602137400.descr: Take a family in desperate need of help in their home. Add some local tradesmen, lot's of generosity and a bucket load of community spirit. You've got yourself the recipe for DIY SOS. Nick Knowles, along with him team of home improvement experts, and lot's of happy volunteers from the communities of Britain pitch in to make life changing modifications to the homes of families who need them most.

1602146100.title: Father Brown
1602146100.descr: Father Brown tries to solve a case of a former hangman Henry Lee, who is found poisoned with hemlock. Will father Brown be able to discover who is the culprit?

1602181800.title: Doctors
1602181800.descr: British medical soap drama about the staff in an NHS doctor's surgery, along with their family and friends in the fictional town of Letherbridge, West Midlands. As well as dealing with patients in and out of the surgery, the staff have constant problems of their own, making it almost impossible to separate work life from personal life.

1602183600.title: Ordinary Lies
1602183600.descr: Drama and deceit lurks in every corner of the shop floor and office in Ordinary Lies, with employees concealing dark secrets from their coworkers. Each episode focusses on an individual employee and their personal tribulations, with their lies spiralling out of control and causing dire repercussions. Series one focusses on the workers at JS Motors, a car showroom, with series two focussing on Coopers Outdoors, a sports-goods store.

1602186900.title: The Musketeers
1602186900.descr: A contemporary take on the well-known story of Alexandre Dumas' Athos, Porthos, Aramis, and d'Artagnan, a group of highly trained musketeers loyal to the king and country. Their wits and skills are matched against Milady de Winter, Cardinal Richelieu, and Comte de Rochefort as they strive to thwart the plots against the crown.

1602189900.title: Doctor Who
1602189900.descr: Peter Capaldi, Pearl Mackie, Matt Lucas, Kieran Bew, Justin Salinger, Peter Caulfield. "Space – the final frontier. Final because it wants to kill us." Trapped on a space station with no oxygen, the Doctor, Bill and Nardole are horrified to discover the automated spacesuits keeping them alive are also trying to kill them!
